{{Taxobox | name = ''Scalindua brodae'' | image = | status = | status_system = | regnum = [[Bacteria]] | phylum = [[Planctomycetes]] | classis = [[Planctomycetia]] | ordo = [[Planctomycetales]] | familia = [[Brocadiaceae]] | genus = ''[[Scalindua]]'' | species = '''''S. brodae''''' | binomial = ''Candidatus'' Scalindua brodae | binomial_authority = Schmid et al. 2003 }}
"'''''[[Candidatus]]''''' '''Scalindua brodae'''" is a [[bacterial]] member of the order [[Planctomycetes]]<ref name="SchmidWalsh2003">{{cite journal|last1=Schmid|first1=Markus|last2=Walsh|first2=Kerry|last3=Webb|first3=Rick|last4=Rijpstra|first4=W. Irene|last5=van de Pas-Schoonen|first5=Katinka|last6=Verbruggen|first6=Mark Jan|last7=Hill|first7=Thomas|last8=Moffett|first8=Bruce|last9=Fuerst|first9=John|last10=Schouten|first10=Stefan|last11=Sinninghe Damsté|first11=Jaap S.|last12=Harris|first12=James|last13=Shaw|first13=Phil|last14=Jetten|first14=Mike|last15=Strous|first15=Marc|title=Candidatus "Scalindua brodae", sp. nov., Candidatus "Scalindua wagneri", sp. nov., Two New Species of Anaerobic Ammonium Oxidizing Bacteria|journal=Systematic and Applied Microbiology|volume=26|issue=4|year=2003|pages=529–538|issn=0723-2020|doi=10.1078/072320203770865837|pmid=14666981}}</ref> and therefore lacks [[peptidoglycan]] in its [[cell wall]], has a compartmentalized [[cytoplasm]]. It is an [[ammonium]] oxidising bacteria.
